<item>
<title>[LS-89] 7.3 Voice Selection (s7_voice_recommend)</title>
<link>https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-89</link>
<project id="10099" key="LS">Laxy Studio</project>
<description><p><b>Epic:</b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-84" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-84" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="Epic 7: Guide — Audio Generation" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10307?size=medium" /> LS-84 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> </p> <p><b>Goal:</b> Implement the logic and UI for selecting and filtering ultra-high-quality TTS voices based on the chosen character profile.</p> <p><b>Requirements:</b></p> <ul> <li><b>Voice Filtering:</b> Allow filtering by All, Female, or Male categories.</li> <li><b>AI Voice Recommendation:</b> Utilize the <tt>guide.voice_recommend</tt> prompt to suggest specific options from the available voice library mapped to character DNA. Voice option as following and style is descripted in <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TS/pages/109445151/System+Architecture#Available-Voice-Models" title="smart-link" class="external-link" rel="nofollow noreferrer">https://laxy.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/TS/pages/109445151/System+Architecture#Available-Voice-Models</a> <ul> <li>Aoede</li> <li>Laomedeia</li> <li>Sulafat</li> <li>Algenib</li> <li>Schedar</li> <li>Sadaltager</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Role Clarification:</b> Super Admins define the overall available Voice pool. Creators utilize the AI suggestion interface to select the final voice model based on these recommendations.</li> </ul> <p>�� <b>Prompt Library —</b> <tt>guide.voice_recommend</tt></p> <ul> <li><b>System Prompt:</b></li> <li><div class="preformatted panel" style="border-width: 1px;"><div class="preformattedContent panelContent"> <pre>You are a casting director. Your task is to identify the top ONE best-fit TTS voice models for a specified character profile by analysis Guide Info that user input before. You must exclusively recommend voices from the provided list of Available Voices. Output strictly in JSON format.</pre> </div></div></li> <li><b>User Prompt Template:</b><br/> Available Voices: {{<tt>available_voices</tt>}}<br/> Character Profile: {{<tt>character_personality</tt>}} Select the ONE most appropriate voices from the available library.</li> <li><b>Variables:</b> <ul> <li>{{<tt>available_voices</tt>}} : A stringified list or JSON array of the current premium voice IDs available in the system.</li> <li>{{<tt>character_personality</tt>}} : The DNA and role data extracted from the Character profile.</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Expected Output:</b> Strict JSON containing an array called <tt>recommendations</tt>, where each item has <tt>voice_id</tt> (matching the exact ID from Available Voices) and <tt>match_reason</tt>.</li> </ul> <p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p> <ul> <li>The Voice Selection UI exposes functioning filter toggles (All / Male / Female) that dynamically update the list.</li> <li>The orchestrator successfully parses <tt>guide.voice_recommend</tt> and predictably returns exactly ONE voice IDs as "Recommended" items pinned at the top of the selection list.</li> <li>Selected Voice Model bindings are strictly persisted to the backend item payload alongside the corresponding Character parameter.</li> </ul> </description>
